</ul>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2">
<h2 id="Awards_and_honors">Awards and honors</h2>
<span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Katharine_Hayhoe&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Awards and honors"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>
</div>
<ul>
<li>Katharine Hayhoe is the recipient of the Lifetime Achievement Award (<a href="/wiki/Champions_of_the_Earth" title="Champions of the Earth">Champions of the Earth</a>) in 2019.<sup id="cite_ref-55" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-55"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>55<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</li>
<li>
<a href="/wiki/United_Nations" title="United Nations">United Nations</a> <a href="/wiki/Champions_of_the_Earth" title="Champions of the Earth">Champions of the Earth</a>, 2019<sup id="cite_ref-:1_56-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:1-56"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>56<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-57" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-57"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>57<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</li>
<li>
<i><a href="/wiki/Foreign_Policy" title="Foreign Policy">Foreign Policy</a></i> magazine 100 Leading Global Thinkers, 2019<sup id="cite_ref-58" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-58"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>58<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</li>
<li>
<a href="/wiki/Stephen_Schneider_(scientist)" title="Stephen Schneider (scientist)">Stephen H. Schneider</a> Award for Outstanding Science Communication, 2018<sup id="cite_ref-59" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-59"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>59<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</li>
<li>
<a href="/wiki/Fortune_(magazine)" title="Fortune (magazine)"><i>Fortune</i></a> magazine's 50 World's Great Leaders, 2017<sup id="cite_ref-60" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-60"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>60<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</li>
<li>
<a href="/wiki/National_Center_for_Science_Education" title="National Center for Science Education">National Center for Science Education</a> Friend of the Planet award, 2016<sup id="cite_ref-61" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-61"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>61<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</li>
<li>
<a href="/wiki/Time_(magazine)" title="Time (magazine)"><i>Time</i></a> magazine's 100 Most Influential People, 2014<sup id="cite_ref-:2_62-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:2-62"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>62<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-:3_63-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:3-63"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>63<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-64" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-64"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>64<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
